[[PageOutline]]
= Claypool Api Application =
----

== Static Methods ==
----

=== getContext ===
The preferred way to get at the Application Context is to use $.$, however you can always directly access it using this static method.
{{{
var appContext = $.Application.getContext(); 
var myAppComponent = appContext.get('myAppComponent');
}}}
which in turn would be the same as
{{{
var myAppComponent = $.$('myAppComponent');
}}}
----

=== Initialize ===
- This function is usually executed inside the standard jQuery $(document).ready() routine.
||=name||=type||=required||=description||
||callback 	||Function ||false 	||An optional callback executed after the event 'claypool:initialize' is triggered but before 'ApplicationLoaded' is triggered.||
{{{
$(document).ready(function(){
	$.Application.Initialize(function(){
		//configure additional libraries here before the "ApplicationLoaded" event
	});
});
}}}
----

=== Reinitialize ===
- Searches the Application Context for an item stored by the given id.
||=name||=type||=required||=description||
||callback 	||Function ||false 	||An optional callback executed after the event 'claypool:reinitialize' is triggered but before 'ApplicationReloaded' is triggered.||
{{{
$.Application.Initialize(function(){
	//reset additional libraries here before the "ApplicationReloaded" event
});
}}}
----